Journalist Deniz Yücel's release from Turkish prison last week was celebrated by many across Germany's political spectrum, with one exception — the populist Alternative for Germany (AfD). Over the past year, while the German-Turkish journalist was in prison, the AfD and other far-right groups have voiced criticism of his work, with AfD parliamentary party leader Alice Weidel calling him an "anti-German hate preacher." Send  Facebook   Twitter   Google+   Whatsapp   
