  Tumblr   linkedin   stumble   Digg   reddit   Newsvine Permalink http://p.dw.com/p/2rBgG Yücel's column looked at Germany's decades of sluggish fertility rates and aging population — a popular topic among columns at the time. Twisting Sarrazin's premise, Yücel titled his column: "Super, Germany is doing away with itself!" "The coming departure of the Germans, however, is the best side of a Völkersterben [roughly translated, the death of a people]," he wrote in the column. Yücel followed the sentence by noting Germany's dark World War II history but also poked fun at the stereotypical "boundless self-pity" and "perpetual bad moods" of Germans. Read more: AfD censures firebrand Andre Poggenburg over anti-Turkish remarks In the piece, he also joked that statistics show the "East Germans will be the first to do away with themselves." The AfD pulled strong support in last year's general election from Germany's eastern states. The second article that the AfD takes issue with is one that Yücel wrote about Sarrazin in 2012, in which he said he hoped the author would have a stroke. The following year, a German court ordered taz to pay Sarrazin €20,000 ($24,600) in damages over the article. After taz, Yücel worked as a Turkey correspondent for the German newspaper Welt, where he wrote critically about President Recep Tayyip Erdogan's policies following a 2016 failed military coup. Read more: Germany's AfD to open its own newsroom in preparation for mainstream media offensive The AfD's Weidel also took aim at Yücel's dual national status, saying that he "shouldn't actually have German citizenship" Critics decry parliament debate as threat to press freedom The head of the German Federation of Journalists (DJV) harshly criticized the AfD for holding a parliamentary debate regarding Yücel's work. "It's downright absurd that the AfD wants to use the Bundestag as a stage for their disturbed relationship to press freedom and freedom of expression," DJV chairman Frank Überall said on Wednesday. Send  Facebook   Twitter   Google+   Whatsapp   
